text:
I was told by recruiting agency that my requested salary is too much for me not having university degree. I am making that much already | Since my current job sucks ass, i decided to be in search of new jobs. A lot of them is through recruiting agency (why would you invest in good running HR and recruitment process when you can cut it to 3rd party), Most of them is sleazy and basically tell you what you want to hear, because they are profit of your salary.

&#x200B;

I applied for a job and got a call from young lady (based on the voice), who is asking me a few info, which is already in the CV. Then she ask for my requested salary. Since I am already making good buck , i said that i am happy to continue with my sum. She basically call me liar, since no one without degree would make that much and no one in right mind would hire me. I just smile and told her that is  my salary in last 2 years and told her that i am not correct person for them then
